risks to avoid`: common wrong turns, scope creep, or implementation shortcuts that should block promotion\\n\\n## Queue Maintenance Rules\\n\\n- keep every non-hardening task focused on one primary product spec\\n- do not leave completed task contracts in this directory\\n- review supporting product, frontend, architecture, and design docs before adding or revising task pages\\n- add UI screenshot, responsive, and accessibility checks to UI-heavy tasks before promotion work starts\\n- external-client behavior such as MCP, REST, Basic Auth, or OAuth must have E2E proof before promotion\\n\\n## When this queue ends\\n\\nWhen the active sequence is exhausted, do not continue with ad hoc prompts alone.\\nUpdate the relevant product specs and design docs first, then seed the next active queue for the next feature wave.\\n\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n./state/artifacts/20260505T175651-endpoint-domain-and-schema/evaluator.log:1578:./state/artifacts/20260505T170817-endpoint-domain-and-schema/worker.jsonl:60:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_30\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc 'rg \\\"bootstrap-state|createPrismaClient|DATABASE_URL|Prisma\\\" -n .'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"./AGENTS.md:22:- TypeScript domain/services with Prisma SQLite persistence\\n./AGENTS.md:46:- Prisma plus SQLite for migrations, seed defaults, and persistent runtime state\\n./lib/db/client.ts:1:import { PrismaBetterSqlite3 } from \\\"@prisma/adapter-better-sqlite3\\\";\\n./lib/db/client.ts:2:import { PrismaClient } from \\\"@prisma/client\\\";\\n./lib/db/client.ts:4:export const DEFAULT_DATABASE_URL = \\\"file:./data/runtime.sqlite\\\";\\n./lib/db/client.ts:7:  return process.env.DATABASE_URL ?? DEFAULT_DATABASE_URL;\\n./lib/db/client.ts:10:export function createPrismaClient() {\\n./lib/db/client.ts:11:  const adapter = new PrismaBetterSqlite3({ url: getDatabaseUrl() });\\n./lib/db/client.ts:12:  return new PrismaClient({ adapter });\\n./