xchange and signed JWT access tokens with endpoint permission claims.\n./state/artifacts/20260505T175651-endpoint-domain-and-schema/evaluator.log:2495:docs/exec-plans/active/019-oauth-mcp-rest-permission-enforcement.md:36:Validate Bearer tokens and enforce endpoint permissions on MCP and REST routes, with correct 401 versus 403 behavior.\n./state/artifacts/20260505T175651-endpoint-domain-and-schema/evaluator.log:2496:docs/exec-plans/active/019-oauth-mcp-rest-permission-enforcement.md:47:- `/mcp/oauth` requires valid Bearer tokens.\n./state/artifacts/20260505T175651-endpoint-domain-and-schema/evaluator.log:2497:docs/exec-plans/active/019-oauth-mcp-rest-permission-enforcement.md:48:- `/mcp` uses Bearer precedence for Bearer headers and rejects invalid Bearer tokens.\n./state/artifacts/20260505T175651-endpoint-domain-and-schema/evaluator.log:2511:tokens used\n./state/artifacts/20260505T173402-endpoint-domain-and-schema/evaluator.log:175:- SQLite is the source of truth for endpoints, parameters, cases, users, clients, codes, tokens, audit events, and settings\n./state/artifacts/20260505T173402-endpoint-domain-and-schema/evaluator.log:178:- issued token records store jti and metadata; raw tokens are shown only at issuance unless explicitly configured\n./state/artifacts/20260505T173402-endpoint-domain-and-schema/evaluator.log:314:- issue mock OAuth tokens with endpoint-level permissions through browser consent or client credentials\n./state/artifacts/20260505T173402-endpoint-domain-and-schema/evaluator.log:394:- OAuth permission behavior needs E2E proof before promotion: allowed endpoint succeeds, denied endpoint returns `403`, revoked/expired/invalid token returns `401`.\n./state/artifacts/20260505T173402-endpoint-domain-and-schema/evaluator.log:1525:tokens used\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
